Hello again, this is my latest creation fy_mystery.  I've learned a lot since my past release's and I've put my new skills to use in this piece.  Ambient sounds, 3dskybox, strategic layout, fog,  realistic displacements, and creativity all came into play.  It's a smaller map but with options, many different ways to play it.

I made the lighting just dark enough that night vision can be useful, but just bright enough where you can see without it.  

I've playtested it quite a bit and it is very enjoyable, I hope you give it a try.  Even worked well 1v1 even though it was a little big.  I like making FY's because they can be used for a regular CS:S and Gun Game.

Special thanks to the people who helped me test it and to interlopers.net forums for the great tutorials and troubleshooting assistance.

**fy_mysterium**

This map is originally based on same sort of style I made years back, but this more of a modern updated version and ive chucked in afew more things to make it just the extra bit more fun and rearanged things to make it user friendly.

In this map you have to choices either side, Maze. or Traps. For maze you must run through a big maze until you find the door to the inner court yard where you will meet up with other members of your team or other people from the oposite team, In the inner courtyard you have ak's and m4a1's and 4 scouts located on the top of the tower. For traps you must go through 6 traps without dieing then you are teleported to the inner courtyard, Once you get to know the maze it may be faster, but the traps are alot more fun and challenging. Enjoy!

This map was created in honor of Aqua Teen Hunger Force, and the best 2-D charactures ever created "The Mooninites".

Installation:

Just place or extract the cstrike folder into your Counter-Strike: Source directory. For example place the files in these directories: "C:\Program Files/Steam/steamapps/"your user name"/counter strike source/cstrike/maps/.../models/...materials/" The "...'s" being each sub folder inside the the main folder tiled "cstrike."

-----------------------------
NOTES:

This is a remake of fy_mm4a1 from CS 1.6 to Counter-Strike: SOURCE. Its not a perfect remake I just did the best I could from memory. 

-------------------------------

Description:

Its a very plain map so just cause its a source remake dosen't mean I made it all super awesome or nothing. But it looks nicer then before(graphix wise) 

 +Works with bots 

 +Has like 32, 16vs16, spawn points

 +Comes with a few different weapons

 +Granades and AWP's are on the top bridge over looking the fighting area
 
 +Boxs and bushes are now in the map
